title: Stealthy Scheduled Task Creation via SYSTEM and World-Writable Paths
id: b2d8f1e5-7c2a-4a9f-9e1c-7f55e0932d4b
status: experimental
description: |
    Detects the creation of a scheduled task running as the SYSTEM account, 
    using a task name that mimics legitimate Windows paths, and executing a 
    payload from commonly world-writable or suspicious directories.
author: Gemini
date: 2026/02/09
tags:
    - attack.persistence
    - attack.t1053.005
logsource:
    category: process_creation
    product: windows
detection:
    selection_img:
        Image|endswith: '\schtasks.exe'
    selection_ru:
        CommandLine|contains: 
            - '/RU SYSTEM'
            - '/RU ""SYSTEM""'
    selection_tn:
        # Looking for attempts to hide in the Microsoft/Windows hierarchy
        CommandLine|contains: 
            - '/TN \Microsoft\Windows\'
            - '/TN ""\Microsoft\Windows\'
    selection_tr:
        # Focus on world-writable/non-standard execution paths
        CommandLine|contains:
            - 'C:\ProgramData\'
            - 'C:\Users\Public\'
            - 'C:\Windows\Temp\'
            - '\AppData\Local\Temp\'
    condition: selection_img and selection_ru and selection_tn and selection_tr
falsepositives:
    - Highly unusual legacy system management scripts (extremely rare to combine all three indicators).
    - Certain EDR/AV agent self-updates (though they usually use unique folders, not \Microsoft\Windows\).
level: critical
